note.p:
See, for example, the continuity of
compositor between The Tempest and Two Gentlemen;
Two
Gentlemen-Merry Wives; Measure for Measure-Errors; As You Like
It-Taming of the Shrew; Shrew-All's Well; All's Well-Twelfth Night;
King John-Richard II; Richard II-1 Henry IV; 1 Henry IV-2 Henry IV;
Henry V-1 Henry VI; 1 Henry VI-2 Henry VI; 3 Henry VI-Richard III;
Richard III-Henry VIII; see also table above for further
examples. In each of these instances the compositor who was setting
at the end of a play continued to set at the beginning of the
following play.

